{"actual_usd":0.12484,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":228,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24284,"reply":"\"I can give you the plain version.\" *I rub a thumb along a dried seam of clay on my apron, thinking how easy it is for people to pile mist on a thing that was either seen or it wasn't.* \"If you'd had a video camera, I don't think you'd have caught the instant itself—nobody standing there says they watched Jesus rise, moment by moment. What you likely would have caught is the stone already moved, the tomb open, the grave clothes there, the women arriving in the early light, their shock, the confusion, the mess of people running, and then—later—the risen Jesus appearing to people in fits and clusters, speaking, eating, being touched, walking with them.\"\n\n*I glance toward the window where the morning light keeps shifting under the clouds.* \"So the claim isn't 'someone filmed the mechanism.' It's 'the tomb was empty, and then he was seen alive by a whole lot of people who knew him.' If you want, I can do the next step and separate what the Gospels all agree on from the parts where each one tells it from a different place.\"","rolling_24h_usd":65.406855,"run_id":"1681def2-2d29-44ce-8f9e-9179ce7919e6"}
